  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a **prinsendaalder** — a large silver coin struck in 1584 at the Dordrecht mint, bearing the portrait of **William the Silent (Willem van Oranje)** with a sword over his shoulder. It is the **only official Dutch coin to depict William of Orange**, and the 1584 date places it at the exact historical fulcrum of his assassination on **10 July 1584** by Balthasar Gerard. The coin was designed as political propaganda by the States of Holland, intended to facilitate William's formal inauguration as sovereign — which never took place. Dies were engraved by **Gerard van Bylaer**, one of the most important medallists of the Dutch Revolt, and the coin was produced under mint master **Jacob Janszoon de Jonge** at the Dordrecht mint, which had operated continuously since 1367.",
      "classified_as": [
        {
          "id": "http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300411780",
          "_label": "description"
        }
